The paper deals with questions of computability and complexity in the Blum-Shub-Smale model of computation on the real numbers, which is a topic that falls under the scope of theoretical computer science. Specifically, the paper discusses the relative computability of sets of algebraic real numbers and the halting problem for BSS-computation, which are topics that are commonly studied in the sub-categories of computability theory (cs.CC), logic in computer science (cs.LO), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), scientific computing (cs.SC), and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories that this paper belongs to, ordered from most to least likely.
